My buddies and I arrived in Williamsburg 1 hour early for a meeting with a few of us. We were also going to have something to eat as well.  Being that we got there 1 hour earlier,  and we were starving and could not wait. I remembered a couple of years ago, this place had good chuletas (pork chips). We got there and they were just about to open..literally turning the key in the door.  The owner i believe was not in a good, given probably the corona virus times and it was Sunday morning.  Later he actually was a good guy but was focusing and putting tables outside for customers.  William, who in1st spoke to about the pork chips was enthusiastic to whip up a plate for me. What annice guy.  Since we were going to be hurried, we decided to also get some beers on tap. Their tap was off, unfortunately because they had a variety of good beers on tap. We had to choose beers they had in bottles. They poured out the beers into plastic cups with lids so we can be outside. Those different beers we got including Coors light, Guiness and Modelo were iced cold!!! Now thats how you give a beer to customers.  The bartender was so sweet. I believe her name was Vivian, she came outside to check on us a couple  of times and also brought the food to the table. The pork chops came, we had also ordered fried plantains, (tostones) and the plate came with a perfect avocado. The pork chip was perfectly fried with no oil on it, and the tastings were crisp and they came with supportive sauces to add to their flavors. Since we could not stay, we felt bad to leave but we will make plans to return another day because of their friendly attitudes.  They have plenty of outdoor seating and inwould recommend going there for food and ice cold beers!!

First time at an Abbas, Was in there about a week ago. Service from hostesses amazing. Server amazing! I was very annoyed that my margarita came after my entree, when that’s the first thing you order. It’s like receiving chips and salsa after you’ve already eaten. I got the taco platter and it wasn’t what I thought It was going to be, the beans tasted weird. And the taco not that amazing. I honestly would’ve  preferred filbertos with a margarita I made over this anyday. Again the server and hostesses were so nice and it’s not their fault they have no control over the quality of food and the way food is being brought out.

We stumbled in here on a Sunday evening after having brunch right down the block. So we did have a couple of drinks before coming here. My wife and all of her friends are Dominican and this had to be one of the only Dominican spots in Williamsburg. We had a blast. The drinks are on point and cost was on par with any other place. They had a live Tipico band. I'm not Dominican but I can dance. This place was lit. I would definitely go back.

This was our last stop after a friday night of bar hopping. We closed out this place! It wasn't until the next day I notice I lost my wallet, only finding the CCard I use to pay for everything! Long story short I met up with a few friends back at Abba's the following day Sunday. I just so happened to ask if anyone had found a wallet. To my disbelief they said YES! They handed me back my wallet with CASH and all!!! I was told the cleaning crew found it and held it for me. I happily tipped the man who found it! Good food, music, hooka and best of all staff!
